<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,428,599]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
Remarks.—The tribe was erected recently based on a five gene phylogenetic tree to based on a deep origin within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buckton" authorityYear="1890" box="[193,333,464,490]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadettinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cicadettinae</taxonomicName>
for the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant, 1906" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1906" box="[497,791,464,490]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Nelcyndana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[497,631,464,490]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Nelcyndana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[639,791,464,490]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refId="ref68457" refString="Distant, W. L. (1906) A synonymic catalogue of Homoptera. Part I. Cicadidae. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 207 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8554" type="book" year="1906">Distant, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, D. C. &amp; Moulds, M. S. &amp; Hill, K. B. R. &amp; Price, B. W. &amp; Wade, E. J. &amp; Owen, C. J. &amp; Goemans, G. &amp; Marathe, K. &amp; Sarkar, V. &amp; Cooley, J. R. &amp; Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Kunte, K. &amp; Villet, M. H. &amp; Simon, C." box="[806,1056,464,491]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref69587" refString="Marshall, D. C., Moulds, M. S., Hill, K. B. R., Price, B. W., Wade, E. J., Owen, C. J., Goemans, G., Marathe, K., Sarkar, V., Cooley, J. R., Sanborn, A. F., Kunte, K., Villet, M. H. &amp; Simon, C. (2018 b) A molecular phylogeny of the cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) with a review of tribe and subfamily level classification. Zootaxa, 4424 (1), 1 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4424.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">
Marshall 
<emphasis box="[916,966,464,490]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">et al</emphasis>
. 2018b
</bibRefCitation>
). The upper pygofer lobe is small and superimposed over the unornamented basal pygofer lobe and is unique to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall &amp; Moulds" authorityYear="2018" box="[1077,1228,500,526]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Nelcyndanini">Nelcyndanini</taxonomicName>
along with the divided uncus that has migrated to the lateral extremities of abdominal segment 10 to appear that they are accessories to the claspers (
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, D. C. &amp; Moulds, M. S. &amp; Hill, K. B. R. &amp; Price, B. W. &amp; Wade, E. J. &amp; Owen, C. J. &amp; Goemans, G. &amp; Marathe, K. &amp; Sarkar, V. &amp; Cooley, J. R. &amp; Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Kunte, K. &amp; Villet, M. H. &amp; Simon, C." box="[326,572,572,599]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref69587" refString="Marshall, D. C., Moulds, M. S., Hill, K. B. R., Price, B. W., Wade, E. J., Owen, C. J., Goemans, G., Marathe, K., Sarkar, V., Cooley, J. R., Sanborn, A. F., Kunte, K., Villet, M. H. &amp; Simon, C. (2018 b) A molecular phylogeny of the cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) with a review of tribe and subfamily level classification. Zootaxa, 4424 (1), 1 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4424.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">
Marshall 
<emphasis box="[434,483,572,598]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">et al</emphasis>
. 2018b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
